  "summary": "This build presents a clean, restrained single-column todo interface with strong alignment, sensible hierarchy, and consistent component styling. System feedback is partly effective: the API health dot and prominent error banner make failure states obvious, and focus treatments are clearly defined across key controls. However, loading feedback, error prevention, and power-user efficiency are weak, with no evident retry flow, undo, shortcut support, or explicit validation before submit. An empty state message exists in the DOM, but the captured screens show only a failed-load state, so confidence on some behavioral states is moderate.",
  "top_strengths": [
    "Clean, well-aligned single-column layout with restrained visual styling",
    "Prominent error banner and API health indicator communicate failures quickly",
    "Clear focus styles on inputs and buttons support keyboard navigation"
  ],
  "top_issues": [
    "Loading and busy states rely mostly on opacity with no explicit progress text or spinner",
    "Little visible error prevention or recovery beyond dismissing the error banner",
    "Efficiency and control features like undo, retry, shortcuts, or bulk actions are absent"
  ]
